messages.message:
I’m running `make clean build mypy` in `api-server-apps` but I’m getting:

```instabase/server/__init__.py: error: Source file found twice under different module names: 'py.instabase.server' and 'instabase.server'
Found 1 error in 1 file (checked 847 source files)```
not sure what’s going on here. I tried reinstalling mypy and deleting my cache. Seems so far I can build api-server-apps locally alright. when i run tests there are also a lot of errors. didn’t have this issue before the holidays
This happens to me once in a while but I forget how I fixed it :grimacing: it had something to do with rogue `___init___.py`  files
which version of mypy do you have installed?
curious if it’s an init py issue, why nobody else is seeing this
You should have mypy 0.701 I believe
